  "segments": [
    {
      "id": "s001",
      "text": "Do you call that a hat?",
      "translation": {
        "text": "你把那个叫帽子吗？"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s002",
      "text": "First listen, and then answer the question.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "先听录音，然后回答问题。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s003",
      "text": "What kind of shopping does the writer enjoy, do you think?",
      "translation": {
        "text": "你认为作者喜欢哪一种购物？"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s004",
      "text": "Do you call that a hat?",
      "translation": {
        "text": "“你把那个叫帽子吗？”"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s005",
      "text": "I said to my wife.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "我对妻子说。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s006",
      "text": "You needn't be so rude about it!",
      "translation": {
        "text": "“你不必这么没礼貌！”"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s007",
      "text": "My wife answered as she looked at herself in the mirror.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "妻子一边照镜子一边回答。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s008",
      "text": "I sat down on one of those modern chairs with holes in it and waited.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "我坐在一把带孔的现代椅子上等着。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s009",
      "text": "We had been in the hat shop for half an hour, and my wife was still in front of the mirror.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "我们在帽子店里已经待了半个小时，妻子仍站在镜子前。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s010",
      "text": "We mustn't buy things we don't need, I remarked suddenly.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "“我们不该买不需要的东西，”我突然说道。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s011",
      "text": "I regretted saying it almost at once.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "话一出口我几乎立刻就后悔了。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s012",
      "text": "You needn't have said that, my wife answered.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "“你本来不必说这句话，”妻子回答，"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s013",
      "text": "I needn't remind you of that terrible tie you bought yesterday.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "“我不必提醒你昨天买的那条糟糕的领带吧。”"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s014",
      "text": "I find it beautiful, I said.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "“我觉得它很漂亮，”我说，"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s015",
      "text": "A man can never have too many ties.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "“男人有再多领带也不嫌多。”"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s016",
      "text": "And a woman can't have too many hats, she answered.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "“女人有再多帽子也不嫌多，”她回答。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s017",
      "text": "Ten minutes later, we walked out of the shop together.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "十分钟后，我们一起走出了商店。"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s018",
      "text": "My wife was wearing a hat that looked like a lighthouse.",
      "translation": {
        "text": "妻子戴着一顶看起来像灯塔的帽子。"
      }
    }
  ],
